title: UP: Kanpur-Bhiwani Kalindi Express collides with goods train at Tundla station, derails | Zee News
text:
Tundla: Delhi-bound Kanpur-Bhiwani Kalindi Express collided with a freight train at Tundla junction in Uttar Pradesh in the early hours of Monday. 
The train number 14723 Kanpur-Bhiwani Kalindi Express collided with the goods train near Agra crossing. 
The incident took place around 2:00 a.m. which affected the rail route between Delhi and Howrah. Uttar Pradesh: Kalindi Express collides with a goods train at Tundla Railway Station in Firozabad, no casualties. pic.twitter.com/p7WwBgvCZM 
â€” ANI UP (@ANINewsUP) February 19, 2017 
No casualties have been reported so far.
